<h1>Problem 2055 - Amateurs Geometry Olympiad, P6 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>A triangle \(ABC\) with \(AB < AC\) has circumcenter \(O\). The perpendicular bisector of \(BC\) meets line \(AB,AC\) at \(D,E\) respectively. The circles with diameters \(DE,AO\) meet at two points \(X,Y\). Let \(M\) be the midpoint of \(BC\).</p>
<p>Prove that the circumcircle of triangle \(MXY\) is tangent to the circumcircle of triangle \(ABC\).</p>
